[{"kind":1,"language":"markdown","value":"# Moosebook"},{"kind":1,"language":"markdown","value":"## Description\n\nA Moosebook is a file that allows you to use Pharo from a Notebook.\nYou can compute Pharo code, and get string or png result.\n"},{"kind":1,"language":"markdown","value":"\n## Demo Basic\n\nLet's create a basic Object using Pharo\n"},{"kind":2,"language":"pharo","value":"test := Object new.\r\n\r\nhello := RSCanvas new"},{"kind":1,"language":"markdown","value":"We can also compute numbers"},{"kind":2,"language":"pharo","value":"number := 1 + 1"},{"kind":1,"language":"markdown","value":"> Variables are shared between cells"},{"kind":2,"language":"pharo","value":"number := number + 1"},{"kind":1,"language":"markdown","value":"### Image Roassal\n\nYou can also create image using [Roassal](https://github.com/ObjectProfile/Roassal3)"},{"kind":2,"language":"pharo","value":"RSAnimationExamples new example16Gris"},{"kind":1,"language":"markdown","value":"You can also visualize the above animation with the GTK backend. To do so, select the line and perform `Show the result of selected lines`"},{"kind":1,"language":"markdown","value":"## Let's Analyze a git repository"},{"kind":1,"language":"markdown","value":"First, we load the project MiningSoftwareRepository (you need a moose image)"},{"kind":2,"language":"pharo","value":"\"Can take up to 2 minutes\"\n\nMetacello new\n  repository: 'github://moosetechnology/GitProjectHealth:main/src';\n  baseline: 'GitLabHealth';\n  onConflict: [ :ex | ex useLoaded ];\n  onUpgrade: [ :ex | ex useLoaded ];\n  onDowngrade: [ :ex | ex useLoaded ];\n  load\n\n\"should display BaselineOfGitLabHealth [baseline] from github://moosetechnology/GitProjectHealth:main/src\""},{"kind":1,"language":"markdown","value":"### Import a model\n\nOnce the GitProjectHealth project has been loaded, one has to import the project from the Git server to the Moose image. As of today, we import a group of repositories."},{"kind":2,"language":"pharo","value":"\"Can take several minutes\"\n\n\"Guard to avoid recompute\"\nglhModel ifNil: [ \n\nglhModel := GLHModel new.\n\nglhApi := GitlabApi new\n    privateToken: '<token>';\n    hostUrl: '<host url>';\n    yourself.\n\nglhImporter := GitlabModelImporter new\n    repoApi: glhApi;\n    glhModel: glhModel;\n    withFiles: false.\n\n\n\" <group number> is the ID of the a Group, you can find the number in the webpage of every project and group\"\nglhImporter importGroup: <group number>.\n\n]"},{"kind":1,"language":"markdown","value":"### Analyse a model"},{"kind":1,"language":"markdown","value":"- Who are the users? "},{"kind":2,"language":"pharo","value":"(glhModel allWithType: GLHUser) asArray collect: #name"},{"kind":1,"language":"markdown","value":"- How many project exists?"},{"kind":2,"language":"pharo","value":"(glhModel allWithType: GLHProject) asArray size "},{"kind":1,"language":"markdown","value":"- What is the first project name?"},{"kind":2,"language":"pharo","value":"(glhModel allWithType: GLHProject) asArray first name"},{"kind":1,"language":"markdown","value":"Show me the commit distribution of the first project"},{"kind":2,"language":"pharo","value":"repository := (glhModel allWithType: GLHProject) anyOne repository.\n\n(GLHCommitDistributionVisualization new forCommits: repository commits)"},{"kind":1,"language":"markdown","value":"- What is the pipeline distribution? "},{"kind":2,"language":"pharo","value":"pipelines := (glhModel allWithType: GLHPipeline).\npipelinesGrouped := pipelines groupedBy: #status.\nstartDate := Date year: Date today year month: 1 day: 1.\nstatuses := pipelinesGrouped keys asSortedCollection: [ :a :b | a asString < b asString ].\nweekCountsByStatus := Dictionary new.\nmaxWeek := 1.\n\nstatuses do: [ :status |\n    | counts |\n    counts := Dictionary new.\n    (pipelinesGrouped at: status) do: [ :pipeline |\n        | date weekIndex |\n        date := pipeline created_at.\n\n        (date notNil and: [ date >= startDate ]) ifTrue: [\n            weekIndex := ((date dayOfYear - 1) // 7) + 1.\n            counts at: weekIndex put: ((counts at: weekIndex ifAbsent: [ 0 ]) + 1).\n            maxWeek := maxWeek max: weekIndex ] ].\n    weekCountsByStatus at: status put: counts ].\nstatuses"},{"kind":2,"language":"pharo","value":"weekNumbers := 1 to: maxWeek.\nweekLabels := weekNumbers collect: [ :week | 'S', week asString ].\n\nchart := RSCompositeChart new.\nchart title: 'Pipelines grouped by week since the 1st of january'.\n\ngroupCount := statuses size max: 1.\nbarSize := 5.\nindex := 0.\n\nlb := RSLegend new.\nlb container: chart canvas.\n\nstatuses do: [ :status |\n    | values plot offset |\n    values := weekNumbers collect: [ :week |\n        ((weekCountsByStatus at: status) at: week ifAbsent: [ 0 ]) ].\n\n    plot := RSBarPlot new x: weekNumbers asArray y: values asArray.\n    plot barSize: barSize.\n    offset := (index - ((groupCount + 1) / 2.0)) * barSize.\n    plot barOffset: offset.\n\n    index := index + 1.\n\t \n    chart add: plot.\n\tlb text: status withBoxColor: plot computeColor.\n ].\n\n\nchart horizontalTick\n    doNotUseNiceLabel;\n    numberOfTicks: weekNumbers size;\n    useVerticalLabel.\n\nchart xlabel: 'Semaine'.\nchart ylabel: 'Nombre de pipelines'.\nlb legendDo: [ :shape | shape withBorder; padding: 10; scaleBy: 0.5 ].\nlb location\n    inner; bottom; right; offset: -30.\nlb build.\n\nchart build.\nchart canvas"}]